Privacy Policy

1. Introduction
This Privacy Policy describes how the Flow Fiction Bot ("Bot") collects, uses, and discloses information when you use our services. By using the Bot, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.

2. Information Collection and Use
The Bot collects and uses the following types of information to provide and improve our services:

2.1 Chat Data
What We Collect: The Bot reads the chat messages in the Discord server where it is active.
How We Use It: The Bot uses this data to perform automated functions based on the messages it reads.
3. Data Storage and Security
We take reasonable measures to protect the information collected through the Bot from loss, theft, misuse, and unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, and destruction.

4. Data Sharing and Disclosure
We do not share or disclose your information to third parties except in the following circumstances:

Legal Requirements: If required by law or in response to a legal request.
Service Providers: To service providers who assist us in operating the Bot and providing our services, subject to confidentiality agreements.
5. Children's Privacy
The Bot is not intended for use by individuals under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we become aware that we have inadvertently received personal information from a user under the age of 13, we will delete such information from our records.

6. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page. You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.

7. Contact Us
